category>TIL</category> <category>data engineering</category> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Polars streaming tricks&lt;/h1&gt;</description><link>https://xiaochuany.github.io/blog/2025/04/06/polars-streaming-tricks/</link> <pubDate>Thu, 01 May 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://xiaochuany.github.io/blog/feed_rss_updated.xml">Xiaochuan's blog</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://xiaochuany.github.io/blog/2025/04/06/polars-streaming-tricks/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Build a mortgate calculator with fasthtml</title> <author>Xiaochuan Yang</author> <category>Tutorial</category> <category>dev tools</category> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Build a mortgate calculator with fasthtml&lt;/h1&gt;</description><link>https://xiaochuany.github.io/blog/2025/04/13/mortgate/</link> <pubDate>Tue, 15 Apr 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://xiaochuany.github.io/blog/feed_rss_updated.xml">Xiaochuan's blog</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://xiaochuany.github.io/blog/2025/04/13/mortgate/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Essentials of polars for pandas experts</title> <author>Xiaochuan Yang</author> <category>Tutorial</category> <category>data engineering</category> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Essentials of &lt;code&gt;polars&lt;/code&gt; for &lt;code&gt;pandas&lt;/code&gt; experts&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;!!! abstract &lt;code&gt;pandas&lt;/code&gt; is a standard tool for every data professional, although it does not scale well in production. Yet, being a standard is a strategic position to be, as libraries coming to solve the scale issue tend to meet data professionals where they are, by mimicing the &lt;code&gt;pandas&lt;/code&gt; API (think: &lt;code&gt;dask&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;pyspark.pandas&lt;/code&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;`polars` is a new-ish tool that is probably replacing `pandas` at the time of writing. The goal of this post is to introduce the kind of mindset change needed to fully exploit `polars` in production.&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;</description><link>https://xiaochuany.github.io/blog/2024/12/21/essentials-of-polars-for-pandas-experts/</link> <pubDate>Mon, 07 Apr 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://xiaochuany.github.io/blog/feed_rss_updated.xml">Xiaochuan's blog</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://xiaochuany.github.io/blog/2024/12/21/essentials-of-polars-for-pandas-experts/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Intro to Jax</title> <author>Xiaochuan Yang</author> <category>Tutorial</category> <category>low latency programming</category> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Intro to Jax&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;!!! abstract Mutiple packages came to solve the speed issue of &lt;code&gt;python&lt;/code&gt; in scientific computing. The de facto standard is of course &lt;code&gt;numpy&lt;/code&gt;. Think also &lt;code&gt;numba&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;jax&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;torch&lt;/code&gt; or even a new language :fire: that go beyond what &lt;code&gt;numpy&lt;/code&gt; offers. This post is a quick intro to my personal preference as of Jan 2025. &lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://xiaochuany.github.io/blog/2025/01/12/intro-to-jax/</link> <pubDate>Fri, 31 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://xiaochuany.github.io/blog/feed_rss_updated.xml">Xiaochuan's blog</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://xiaochuany.github.io/blog/2025/01/12/intro-to-jax/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Mini-tutorial for python packaging, release and publish</title> <author>Xiaochuan Yang</author> <category>Tutorial</category> <category>dev tools</category> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Mini-tutorial for python packaging, release and publish&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;!!! abstract  This mini-tutorial is a beginner&#39;s cheatsheet to python packaging. Check &lt;a href=&#34;https://packaging.python.org/en/latest/&#34;&gt;Python packaing user guide&lt;/a&gt; for an authoritative guidance on the topic. &lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://xiaochuany.github.io/blog/2025/01/03/mini-tutorial-for-python-packaging-release-and-publish/</link> <pubDate>Fri, 10 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://xiaochuany.github.io/blog/feed_rss_updated.xml">Xiaochuan's blog</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://xiaochuany.github.io/blog/2025/01/03/mini-tutorial-for-python-packaging-release-and-publish/</guid> </item> </channel></rss>